Cyril Mudiagbe, an aide of the Deputy Senate President and governorship candidate of the All Progressives Congress (APC) in Delta State, Senator Ovie Omo-Agege, has been shot dead. Mudiagbe was killed on Saturday night at his residence in Sapele area of the state, it was learnt.   Buhari celebrates Amusan, Brume over World Athletics feats     FCT taskforce begins massive demolition of…     Property destroyed as fire razes two-storey in Onitsha   A resident of the area, who identified himself as Lucky, said the gunmen “came to rob”. “They first went to the plaza opposite the house before coming to this place,” he said. Police spokesman Bright Edafe said he was yet to be briefed on the incident.